<main>
<section class="editorial-page reveal"><h1>Approach</h1></section>
<section class="method-grid reveal" id="methodology">
<article class="method-card">
<span class="tiny-label">Methodology</span>
<h3>How the studio works</h3>
<p>Each project moves through research, spatial editing, material development, and a calm, highly considered visual language. The goal is not just beauty, but clarity and lived comfort.</p>
</article>
<article class="method-card">
<span class="tiny-label">Framework</span>
<h3>From concept to completion</h3>
<p>We begin with listening, build narrative boards, refine plans, study light, and then layer in objects, art, and styling so the finished space feels inevitable instead of overdone.</p>
</article>
</section>
<section class="approach-block reveal" id="approach-spaces">
<img alt="Spaces approach" decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="assets/interior-14.webp"/>
<div>
<span>01</span>
<h2>Spaces</h2>
<p>Spatial planning is treated as choreography. Circulation, pause points, hosting moments, and intimate corners are balanced so each room feels both functional and emotionally clear.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section class="approach-block reverse reveal" id="approach-art">
<img alt="Art approach" decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="assets/interior-16.webp"/>
<div>
<span>02</span>
<h2>Art</h2>
<p>Art is used as an atmospheric layer. We curate pieces that introduce memory, contrast, stillness, and cultural texture without disrupting the calm of the wider interior composition.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section class="approach-block reveal" id="approach-lighting">
<img alt="Lighting approach" decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="assets/interior-17.webp"/>
<div>
<span>03</span>
<h2>Lighting</h2>
<p>Lighting is considered architecture in its own right. Soft wall glows, task lighting, sculptural fixtures, and concealed illumination work together to define mood and depth.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section class="approach-block reverse reveal" id="approach-styling">
<img alt="Styling approach" decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="assets/interior-18.webp"/>
<div>
<span>04</span>
<h2>Styling</h2>
<p>Styling is deliberate and restrained. Books, florals, textiles, vessels, and table objects are edited carefully so a space feels inhabited, warm, and quietly expressive.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section class="approach-block reveal" id="approach-branding">
<img alt="Branding approach" decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="assets/interior-19.webp"/>
<div>
<span>05</span>
<h2>Branding</h2>
<p>For hospitality and commercial work, spatial branding ensures the interior carries the same clarity as the brand itself—from first impression and signage to texture, scent, and guest memory.</p>
</div>
</section>
</main>
